  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Aviva Partnership: FbA in Indonesia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#xC2;&#xA0;
&#xC2;&#xA0;
Forecast-based Financing (FbF) releases humanitarian funding based on forecasts for pre-agreed activities in anticipation of the occurrence of a disaster. In many cases this action in advance of rather than after a disaster, could reduce suffering, enhance preparedness and response, and contributes to a strengthened community resilience.&#xC2;&#xA0;
&#xC2;&#xA0;
The vision for FbA in Indonesia is to shift the current disaster management mindset of response to a disaster, to one that is &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2DC;response to a forecast&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;-a shift that leverages current capacities and strengths and applies them to anticipatory approaches.
&#xC2;&#xA0;
Support from AVIVA is helping PMI to realise this vision through funding to develop an Early Action Protocol to access funding for imminent threat in advance of a disaster occurring, based on a set of triggers, and pre-defined actions to be taken.</narrative>
  </description>
